WEBVTT

00:05.439 --> 00:06.406 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:06.440 --> 00:07.407 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.441 --> 00:09.209 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Gwen Ifill is away.

00:09.243 --> 00:13.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
Hurricane Matthew
barrels toward Florida, leaving
a path of

00:13.614 --> 00:17.050 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and destruction through Haiti
and Cuba.

00:17.084 --> 00:21.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also ahead this Wednesday: The
presidential
campaigns are back on the trail
following

00:21.688 --> 00:23.924 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the vice presidential debate.

00:23.957 --> 00:27.661 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
How the candidates are
responding to the
hardest-hitting
moments.

00:27.694 --> 00:33.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: In Iraq, militia groups on
the front
lines have become an important
element in

00:33.467 --> 00:35.869 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the fight against ISIS, but at
what cost?

00:35.903 --> 00:39.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BELKIS WILLE, Human Rights
Watch: They have
this ability to carry out these
abuses, to

00:39.506 --> 00:42.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
carry out these revenge attacks,
with complete
impunity.

00:42.976 --> 00:48.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Plus: Florida's
battle against
Zika -- how the mysterious
disease is gaining

00:48.682 --> 00:51.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the state and causing a stir
in affected
neighborhoods.

00:52.019 --> 00:54.354 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JAY ANDERSON, Florida: It's
scary.

00:54.388 --> 00:58.792 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And when you're scared,
especially when you're
scared for your unborn child,
and especially

00:58.825 --> 01:03.297 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when it's your first child, you
try and focus
on what you can control.

01:03.330 --> 01:05.065 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And there's only a few things
that you can.

01:05.098 --> 01:12.906 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:12.940 --> 01:15.742 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:15.776 --> 01:25.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Rescue workers in
Haiti are
struggling to reach victims of
Hurricane Matthew

01:25.819 --> 01:30.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tonight, while officials in the
Southeastern
U.S. are urging residents to get
ready.

01:31.024 --> 01:37.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The big storm is churning north,
with sustained
winds of 120 miles an hour.

01:37.631 --> 01:44.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For Haiti, it shapes up as the
worst disaster
since the devastating earthquake
of 2010.

01:44.037 --> 01:50.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the port city of Les Cayes,
already-flimsy
homes are now piles of debris,
and people

01:50.210 --> 01:52.646 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are wading through knee-deep
water.

01:52.679 --> 01:55.248 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: Our homes are completely
destroyed.

01:55.282 --> 01:57.050 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We have lost everything.

01:57.084 --> 01:59.119 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We need help as fast as
possible.

01:59.152 --> 02:00.921 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We cannot be left behind.

02:00.954 --> 02:06.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Other towns are
cut off, while
the U.N. reports at least 10,000
people are

02:06.326 --> 02:09.930 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in shelters, and hospitals are
full.

02:09.963 --> 02:15.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the capital, Port-au-Prince,
the River
Grise was close to topping its
banks today.

02:15.635 --> 02:19.873 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Charles Patrick Almazor spoke to
us from Port-au-Prince.

02:19.906 --> 02:23.010 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's with Partners in Health, an
international
aid organization.

02:23.043 --> 02:28.715 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CHARLES PATRICK ALMAZOR,
Partners in Health:
Because of the flooding, we
expect more cases

02:28.749 --> 02:31.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of cholera and more cases of
diarrhea-related
diseases.

02:31.184 --> 02:36.289 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, we are trying to get
prepared for that.

02:36.323 --> 02:41.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The disaster
prompted Haitian
officials to postpone the
presidential election,

02:41.928 --> 02:43.930 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
set for next week.

02:43.964 --> 02:49.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From Haiti, the storm rolled
across the sparsely
populated eastern tip of Cuba,
and destroyed

02:49.903 --> 02:51.905 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
dozens of homes in Baracoa.

02:51.938 --> 02:54.608 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): It
was a disaster.

02:54.641 --> 02:56.243 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Everything was a disaster.

02:56.276 --> 02:57.778 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There is nothing left here.

02:57.811 --> 02:59.579 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This was like never seen before.

02:59.613 --> 03:03.216 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Next on Matthew's
path, the
Bahamas.

03:03.250 --> 03:08.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It pounded the southern islands
with heavy
rain all day, and the eye could
reach Nassau

03:08.522 --> 03:10.123 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
tomorrow morning.

03:10.157 --> 03:14.394 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
By Thursday night, the storm is
expected to
be off South Florida.

03:14.428 --> 03:20.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then, over the weekend, it's on
course to
whirl up the East Coast toward
the Carolinas,

03:20.500 --> 03:24.204 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
before veering back out into the
Atlantic.

03:24.237 --> 03:28.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Florida Governor Rick Scott says
the state
may see its largest evacuation
ever.

03:28.809 --> 03:30.744 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

03:30.777 --> 03:33.346 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RICK SCOTT (R), Florida:
Regardless if there's
a direct hit or not, the impacts
will be devastating.

03:33.380 --> 03:38.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I cannot emphasize it enough
that everyone
in our state must prepare now
for a direct

03:38.251 --> 03:40.053 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
hit.

03:40.087 --> 03:44.424 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In South
Carolina, people flocked
for water and supplies today,
and Governor

03:44.458 --> 03:50.697 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Nikki Haley announced a
scaled-back plan to
evacuate a quarter-million
people.

03:50.730 --> 03:54.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama added his own
warning at the
Federal Emergency Management
Agency.

03:54.901 --> 03:57.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
I want to emphasize to the
public this is

03:57.404 --> 03:59.072 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a serious storm.

03:59.106 --> 04:04.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If there is an evacuation order
in your community,
you need to take it seriously.

04:04.077 --> 04:10.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: If it does make
landfall, Matthew
would be the first major
hurricane to strike

04:10.050 --> 04:13.787 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the U.S. mainland since 2005.

04:13.820 --> 04:18.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: The
United Nations
announced the Paris agreement on
climate change

04:18.258 --> 04:20.594 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
will take effect on November 4.

04:20.627 --> 04:25.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It reached the threshold when
more than 55
nations generating at least 55
percent of

04:25.799 --> 04:29.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the planet's greenhouse gas
emissions signed
on.

04:30.003 --> 04:34.407 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama walked out to
the White House
Rose Garden to hail the
development and its

04:34.441 --> 04:35.475 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
implications.

04:35.509 --> 04:38.111 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: Today, the world
meets the moment.

04:38.145 --> 04:43.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And if we follow through on the
commitments
that this Paris agreement
embodies, history

04:43.850 --> 04:48.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
may well judge it as a turning
point for our
planet.

04:48.188 --> 04:52.492 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So,this gives us the best
possible shot to
save the one planet we have got.

04:52.526 --> 04:58.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The agreement
calls for countries
to report progress on reducing
emissions,

04:58.098 --> 05:00.734 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but doesn't set binding limits.

05:00.767 --> 05:06.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.N. Security Council agreed
unanimously
today that Antonio Guterres of
Portugal should

05:06.973 --> 05:10.911 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
be the United Nations' next
leader, its secretary-general.

05:10.944 --> 05:17.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The former prime minister also
served as U.N.
high commissioner for refugees
for 10 years.

05:17.117 --> 05:18.718 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He would succeed Ban Ki-Moon.

05:18.752 --> 05:25.158 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Council votes tomorrow on
recommending
Guterres to the General
Assembly.

05:25.192 --> 05:29.763 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
