responded in
Istanbul that it's much ado
about nothing.

06:06.967 --> 06:10.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MEVLUT CAVUSOGLU, Turkish
Foreign Minister
(through translator): The camp
was set up

06:10.670 --> 06:13.306 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
within the knowledge of Iraqi
administration.

06:13.340 --> 06:17.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Baghdad officials have visited
this camp and
have even provided financial
support to it

06:17.711 --> 06:19.045 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the past.

06:19.079 --> 06:22.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This problem occurred because of
internal
conflict of Iraqi policy.

06:22.382 --> 06:26.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The two nations
are also at
odds over Iraqi plans for
retaking the city

06:27.020 --> 06:28.922 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
