50:58.455 --> 51:01.425 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, here's what this is all
about, phase changes.

51:01.458 --> 51:03.861 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You might remember this from
high school.

51:03.894 --> 51:08.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Phase changes occur -- it's the
difference
between steam becoming --
condensing down

51:08.832 --> 51:12.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to water, and then ultimately
freezing into
a solid.

51:12.202 --> 51:13.938 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Those are phase changes we
understand.

51:13.971 --> 51:18.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When it gets to the quantum
level, the way
things shift from phase to
phase, we don't

51:18.275 --> 51:19.610 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
understand as well.

51:19.643 --> 51:23.080 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As a matter of fact, the quantum
world is
like a parallel universe.

51:23.113 --> 51:26.417 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Things react and do things very
differently.

51:26.450 --> 51:32.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Topology is a technique where
you identify
basic shapes, whether something
has like a

51:32.489 --> 51:35.726 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
single hole or two holes or is
solid.

51:35.759 --> 51:40.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the Nobel Committee used a
pretzel and
a bagel and a muffin to try to
illustrate

51:40.698 --> 51:42.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this point.

51:42.666 --> 51:46.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But by understanding that
mathematics, scientists
hope to get greater insights
into what happens

51:46.937 --> 51:50.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
